-- Seaport Group Buys $412 Million in Lehman Claims From Italian Insurer
-- Linda Sandler
-- 2010-06-18T13:53:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/seaport-group-buys-412-million-in-lehman-claims-from-italian-insurer.html

          
          
             Seaport Group of New York bought
$412 million in claims on bankrupt Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc.
from Italy’s Popolare Vita SpA, according to a court filing. The
purchase price wasn’t disclosed.  
 The claims include zero-coupon Eurodollar notes guaranteed
by Lehman, according to the filings in U.S. Bankruptcy Court in
Manhattan yesterday.  
